# Accepted vulnerabilities.
#
# Every entry here must include:
#   - CVE ID
#   - Which image it affects
#   - Why it is not exploitable in our code paths
#   - An expiration date (`exp:YYYY-MM-DD`) so Trivy re-raises the
#     finding if we forget to revisit it
#
# Before adding a line here, try to fix the vulnerability first — pin a
# newer base image, upgrade a dependency, or swap to a different runtime.
# This file is a last resort for upstream issues that are genuinely not
# exploitable in our context.

# CVE-2026-28390 — OpenSSL NULL pointer dereference DoS via crafted
# Cryptographic Message Syntax (CMS / PKCS#7) structures.
#
# Affects: strait-app runtime image (gcr.io/distroless/nodejs22-debian12)
# via libssl3 3.0.18-1~deb12u2. Fixed upstream in libssl3
# 3.0.19-1~deb12u2 and awaiting rebuild of the Google distroless image.
#
# Strait App is not exploitable: the Node runtime uses libssl only for
# TLS client connections (outbound HTTPS to the Strait API, Resend,
# Stripe, etc.) and the built-in `fetch` for the healthcheck. None of
# those code paths parse CMS. Better Auth signs JWTs via `jose`, which
# does not link against libssl. The Go `strait` image escapes this CVE
# family entirely by using distroless/static-debian12 (no libssl at
# all), which Node cannot do because Node links libssl dynamically.
#
# Reassess on or before the expiration date. If the distroless rebuild
# has landed by then, remove this line.
CVE-2026-28390 exp:2026-05-15
